a) A ∪ B: The union of sets A and B contains all elements that are in either set A or set B or in both. So, A ∪ B = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}

b) A ∩ B: The intersection of sets A and B contains all elements that are in both set A and set B. Since there are no common elements in A and B, A ∩ B = {}

c) A - B: The difference of sets A and B contains all elements that are in set A but not in set B. So, A - B = {2, 4, 6}

d) B - A: The difference of sets B and A contains all elements that are in set B but not in set A. So, B - A = {1, 3, 5}
